onward /ˈɒnwəd/

1. ADJ Onward means moving forward or continuing a journey. 向前的; (旅程) 继续进行的 

例： American Airlines have two flights a day to Bangkok, and there are onward flights to Phnom Penh. 美国航空公司每天有两个航班飞到曼谷，还有接着飞金边的航班。 

2. ADV Onward is also an adverb. 向前地; (旅程) 继续进行地 [ADV after v] 

例： The bus continued onward. 公交车继续前行。 

3. ADJ Onward means developing, progressing, or becoming more important over a period of time. 发展的 

例： ...the onward march of progress in the aircraft industry. …航空工业的发展进程。 

4. ADV Onward is also an adverb. 发展地 [ADV after v] 

例： From here, it has been onward and upward all the way. 由此开始，它一直在发展、高升。 

5. ADV If something happens from a particular time onward or onwards , it begins to happen at that time and continues to happen afterward. 从…以后 ['from' n ADV] 

例： From the turn of the century onward, she shared the life of the aborigines. 从世纪之交以后，她就过着和土著人一样的生活。

